@node ID4_2 "Systemtime (ID4_2)"
From: samwel@algonet.se (Harry Samwel)
Date: Sat, 10 Oct 1998 23:04:30 +0100
Subject: Re: Systemtime

Hello Allister

On 10-Okt-98, you wrote:

> How can I set the SystemTime using Timer.device?
> Since I don't know very much about device programming the autodocs
> didn't heelped me a lot. That's why my question:
> Could anyone send me an example source which does that?

A while back I did this emodule for getting system time..
Setting it must be quite similar I think :)
AmigaE has very good sources about this... I got some good help :)

Hope this helps!

OPT MODULE

MODULE 'devices/timer',
       'exec/ports',
       'exec/io'

EXPORT PROC getSysTime()
DEF secs=0,port:PTR TO mp,tr:PTR TO timerequest
   IF port:=CreateMsgPort()
      IF tr:=CreateIORequest(port,SIZEOF timerequest)
         IF OpenDevice('timer.device',0,tr,0)=0
            tr.io.command:=TR_GETSYSTIME
            DoIO(tr)
            secs:=tr.time.secs
            CloseDevice(tr)
         ENDIF
         DeleteIORequest(tr)
      ENDIF
      DeleteMsgPort(port)
   ENDIF
ENDPROC secs
- --

