me.

I have the need to interface two program which are two real separate
process. This interface should be bidirectional, in the sense that both
programs may receive and send data to the other one. The data to be passed
are pointers to internal (static) data and a notification message is
needed to signal if a pointer has changed.

As an example let's suppose process A has to pass the pointer of one of
its windows to process B after having received a request for that pointer
from B. After that B is able to read (and only read) data from the just
received pointer and do whatever it wants with them (let's suppose it want
to know the window position and size).

I have thought some ways to achieve that task, but probably someone may
suggest some other ways that may be useful to correct/integrate/substitute
the ones I have thought. Note that a simple Arexx or general message port
interface is not possibly the best solution here unless you can come up
with a well organized list of flexible and powerful commands.

Any suggestion appreciated.

Thanks in advance.

M&F

