@node ID24_1 "Reading icon arguments (ID24_1)"
From: jason@fsel.com ("Jason Hulance")
Subject: RE: Reading icon arguments
Date: Tue, 27 Oct 1998 15:49:16 -0000

David Lidstrm wrote:

> I've got a problem with reading tooltypes from icons!!
> On my computer the program works fine, but other people
> says it freaks out when started from WB.

"Freaks out?"  Anything more specific than that?

> This is the wb-part of the procedure that checks the arguments.
>
[...Snip...]
>
>     IF (args.lock) AND (args.name[]>0)

This line might be the problem.  There's an old bug (that Wouter
doesn't seem able to fix) concerning dereferencing object elements
with no explicit PTR type.  If you're using the typed modules (as
in v3.3a, for example) then this isn't the problem, since "name"
in "wbarg" is explicitly typed as "PTR TO CHAR".

Of course, you could try the following, just in case:

    IF (args.lock) AND (Char(args.name)>0)

>            t:=FindToolType(toolarray, 'FONT')
...
>                    MidStr(t, t, 0,i)
>                    StrCopy(font_name, t, ALL)

This is more likely to be the source of the problem.  "t" is the
result of FindToolType(), which is definitely not an Estring, so
you can't use it as the first argument to MidStr().  In fact, you
don't own that memory (the icon.library does) so you shouldn't be
touching the contents.

Replace the MidStr()/StrCopy() pair of lines with:

  StrCopy(font_name, t, i)

