@node ID24_5 "Reading icon arguments (ID24_5)"
Date: Wed, 28 Oct 1998 15:12:54 +0100
From: ss37@irz301.inf.tu-dresden.de (Sven Steiniger)
Subject: Re: Reading icon arguments

I have no manuals here, so just some ideas.

>     IF (args.lock) AND (args.name[]>0)

Doesnt args.name always contain the program-name?
And if not, an StrLen(args.name)>0 would be much
clearer, wouldn't it?

>         IF (args[].name<>0) AND (dobj:=GetDiskObject(args.name))

Suspicious. You test args[].name for not being NIL
but use args.name to get the diskobject! And remember
that this is too much C-like. In E, all expression
(even logical ones) are computed. Means that
it evaluates both args.name<>0 and GetDiskObject(args.name)
and then ANDs both results together. So change this
to
        IF args.name<>NIL
                IF dobj:=GetDiskObject(args.name)

>             t:=FindToolType(toolarray, 'FONT')
>             IF t
>                 i:=InStr(t, '/')
>                 temp:=String(StrLen(t))
>                 IF i>3
>                     MidStr(temp, t, i+1, STRLEN-i)
>                     MidStr(t, t, 0,i)
>                     StrCopy(font_name, t, ALL)
>                     font_size:=Val(temp)
>                 ENDIF

Mmmh. A bit overkilled and 'temp' is not freed.
Try:
                IF i>3
                        StrCopy(font_name, t, i)
                        font_size:=Val(t+i+1)
                ENDIF

And did you set all default-values? Maybe you initialize
the start-values for ReadArgs() correctly and therefore
it works in Cli-mode. But when using tooltypes you only
set those values which are given via tooltypes but didn't
initialize those that are missed.

