@node ID25_7 "Wintel True-Type Fonts (ID25_7)"
Date: 29 Oct 98 01:50:41 -0500
From: victord@netrover.com ("Victor Ducedre")
Subject: Re: Wintel True-Type Fonts

Quoting Maxim Olivier-Adlhoch...

>If I get you right, I open diskfont.library then I Open ttf.library then
>when I use OpenDiskFont from diskfont.library I can use any ttf font!?

>or is there a deamon (Which I must start in WbStartup for example) which
>patches the os's Diskfont into recognizing ttf fonts...

    No daemon is necessary.  The ttf.library adds a new font engine
to the system in the same system-compliant way that is used by the
bullet.library for Compugraphic fonts.  When you install a truetype
font with the included program, it creates the .font and .otag files
that the system uses to determine how to access the font.
    I'm not sure how you'd go about accessing the fonts directly from
your program (off the top of my head, I expect calling OpenDiskFont()
should be enough), but using the ASL font requester provides direct
access to them, and on my A3000/030-25 they are much faster to load than
the Compugraphic variety.

HTH
