ow. :( How about the various options passed to guiinitA()? Is any of
those causing it? Are you using any PLUGINs that haven't been recompiled
against other sources that have changed? (this could probably throw
things off even if they weren't actually used by the program, as EC
would get its offsets in a twist while compiling...) Umm...

The reason I made the above diagnosis is that this (or a crash) is
usually a symptom, for me, of a malformed GUI that's not quite
malformed enough that EasyGUI can detect it... (the pause generally
meaning that the processor has gone somewhere it wasn't meant to
in memory - if it hits an RTS it might be fine, otherwise the program
may hang the machine :)

